        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued August 17 at 6:34PM MDT until August 17 at 7:00PM MDT by NWS Glasgow MT</headline>
        <description>At 629 PM MDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from 22 miles south of Zortman to 6 miles west of
Flatwillow, moving east at 40 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Observed wind gust of 61 mph at 6:30 PM MDT at War Horse NW
Mesonet in west central Petroleum county.

IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

Locations impacted include...
Winnett, Flatwillow, Petrolia Lake, Fred Robinson Bridge, Valentine,
Cat Creek, and Tiegen.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.

Torrential rainfall is occurring with these storms, and may lead to
flash flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.</instruction>
